1
00:00:56,136 --> 00:00:57,775
(Scrapping Wood)

2
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:01,300
It's just a misconception, really.

3
00:01:03,425 --> 00:01:08,925
"Blind people can't truly
grasp the idea of beauty."

4
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:15,800
No, blind folks like me...

5
00:01:16,966 --> 00:01:22,633
...we really think a lot
about what people...

6
00:01:22,716 --> 00:01:26,050
...see as beauty.

7
00:01:26,675 --> 00:01:30,091
I've spent years searching
for that beauty...

8
00:01:30,508 --> 00:01:34,135
...travelling across the country
visiting tombstones and monuments...

9
00:01:34,175 --> 00:01:39,925
...touching and discovering
the beauty our ancestors left behind.

10
00:01:40,716 --> 00:01:43,175
You've been through so much.

11
00:01:43,216 --> 00:01:44,675
Of course, of course.

12
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:49,675
But there's something
I've been curious about.

13
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,258
Your hands are remarkably delicate.

14
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:53,593
- My hands?
- Yes.

15
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:56,633
I expected people who engrave...

16
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:59,425
...to have calloused hands,
but yours are so smooth...

17
00:01:59,466 --> 00:02:02,174
...do you do anything to take care of them?

18
00:02:02,531 --> 00:02:03,797
(Gasps)

19
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:07,636
I take meticulous care of my hands.

20
00:02:07,928 --> 00:02:09,805
These hands...

21
00:02:09,845 --> 00:02:13,720
They're like my eyes...

22
00:02:13,970 --> 00:02:15,970
...you know?

23
00:02:16,011 --> 00:02:19,303
I see and feel through them.

24
00:02:19,678 --> 00:02:22,095
What about that scar?

25
00:02:22,386 --> 00:02:24,636
Oh, this?

26
00:02:25,928 --> 00:02:27,928
I hurt myself when I was young...

27
00:02:28,803 --> 00:02:32,261
For us, learning a job can be hard.

28
00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:36,845
Ordinary people like us
can't even imagine...

29
00:02:36,928 --> 00:02:38,970
...how hard that must have been...

30
00:02:40,345 --> 00:02:44,345
Let's shift gears a bit.

31
00:02:45,803 --> 00:02:48,511
You're a stamp engraving artisan...

32
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,930
...but also a single dad...

33
00:02:50,970 --> 00:02:54,845
...and your son now runs
CHEONGPUNG ENGRAVING.

34
00:02:55,178 --> 00:02:56,678
- Hm?
- Yes.

35
00:02:57,220 --> 00:03:01,346
I think our viewers would be curious
about that part of your life.

36
00:03:01,386 --> 00:03:03,261
Why would they be curious about that?

37
00:03:03,303 --> 00:03:05,678
Raising a child alone is hard enough...

38
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:11,136
...let alone as someone
who's visually impaired.

39
00:03:11,428 --> 00:03:14,470
Everyone tries to raise their kids well,
even in hardship.

40
00:03:14,495 --> 00:03:15,695
(Chuckles)

41
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:20,458
Kids pretty much grow up on
their own if you let them.

42
00:03:20,511 --> 00:03:24,220
Children don't grow up on their own,
you raised him!

43
00:03:24,886 --> 00:03:28,345
That's what we're curious about...

44
00:03:29,011 --> 00:03:35,011
...about your struggles
and the thoughts you had...

45
00:03:37,178 --> 00:03:39,095
It was hard.

46
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:41,553
Yes.

47
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:44,553
What's the use of dwelling on hardships?

48
00:03:44,617 --> 00:03:45,477
(Scoffs)

49
00:03:47,678 --> 00:03:50,220
Feel free to take your time.

50
00:03:50,586 --> 00:03:51,236
(Beep Sound)

51
00:03:51,269 --> 00:03:54,103
The current time is 3:04 p.m.

52
00:03:54,761 --> 00:03:56,928
Dong-hwan, let me take a short break.

53
00:03:57,053 --> 00:03:58,471
Father, they're busy people.

54
00:03:58,511 --> 00:03:59,930
I'm sorry, one moment.

55
00:03:59,970 --> 00:04:01,930
- My apologies.
- We should continue a bit more...

56
00:04:01,970 --> 00:04:04,055
Sorry,
I didn't realize how quickly time flew.

57
00:04:04,095 --> 00:04:05,555
- It was so fascinating.
- Sorry about that.

58
00:04:05,595 --> 00:04:07,761
Let's take a short break, I'm sorry.

59
00:04:07,845 --> 00:04:10,220
- Have a smoke, father.
- Take five, everyone!

60
00:04:10,678 --> 00:04:12,043
Here's the door.

61
00:04:12,102 --> 00:04:13,070
(Sighs)

62
00:04:15,511 --> 00:04:16,845
Commendation.

63
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,664
(Grunts)

64
00:04:18,641 --> 00:04:19,680
(Sighs)

65
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,910
Dong-hwan, your father is truly remarkable.

66
00:04:23,102 --> 00:04:24,141
(Scoffs)

67
00:04:24,785 --> 00:04:27,702
He's more than I could
ever hope to deserve.

68
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:28,912
Just look at this!

69
00:04:28,952 --> 00:04:32,202
"I'm Yeong-gyu is proof
that miracles are real."

70
00:04:32,297 --> 00:04:33,260
(Gasps)

71
00:04:33,285 --> 00:04:35,118
What a headline.

72
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:38,827
What's this?

73
00:04:39,910 --> 00:04:41,078
Oh, that?

74
00:04:41,118 --> 00:04:46,368
It's an old photo from when he
first opened his engraving stand.

75
00:04:47,225 --> 00:04:47,927
(Sighs)

76
00:04:47,952 --> 00:04:50,285
It's the only old photo we have.

77
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:52,960
You look just like him.

78
00:04:53,023 --> 00:04:54,052
(Scoffs)

79
00:04:54,077 --> 00:04:55,410
Well...

80
00:04:56,035 --> 00:05:00,118
...I thought so too, so, a long time ago...

81
00:05:00,618 --> 00:05:04,120
...I told him how much I look like him.

82
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:07,202
What did he say? Was he happy to hear it?

83
00:05:09,202 --> 00:05:11,660
He just stood quietly, thinking.

84
00:05:13,285 --> 00:05:14,868
I guess...

85
00:05:15,993 --> 00:05:20,452
...maybe he was reflecting
on the idea of resemblance...

86
00:05:21,410 --> 00:05:25,535
...since he's been blind from birth.

87
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,118
That's true.

88
00:05:29,702 --> 00:05:32,202
He's never even seen his own face...

89
00:05:32,952 --> 00:05:35,285
...I never thought of it like that.

90
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,202
Where did you put the ashtray?

91
00:05:37,702 --> 00:05:38,993
Here, give it to me.

92
00:05:39,285 --> 00:05:40,578
Have you rested enough, sir?

93
00:05:40,618 --> 00:05:41,329
Oh, yes, yes.

94
00:05:41,369 --> 00:05:43,412
Shall we continue?

95
00:05:43,452 --> 00:05:44,160
Sure.

96
00:05:45,243 --> 00:05:47,493
Let's continue the shoot!

97
00:05:47,785 --> 00:05:50,077
- Camera.
- Coming.

98
00:05:50,102 --> 00:05:51,177
(Footstep)

99
00:05:51,202 --> 00:05:51,871
Sorry about that.

100
00:05:51,911 --> 00:05:53,078
Not at all.

101
00:05:53,118 --> 00:05:55,410
Let's get a close up of his hand.

102
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:58,620
Good to go.

103
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,952
Let's take it slow.

104
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:24,368
THE UGLY

105
00:06:24,393 --> 00:06:26,174
(Liquid Pouring)

106
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:27,409
(Thud)

107
00:06:28,674 --> 00:06:29,799
(Sighs)

108
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:40,967
Father.

109
00:06:42,570 --> 00:06:43,114
Here.

110
00:06:43,154 --> 00:06:44,820
- Tea time already?
- Yes.

111
00:06:46,570 --> 00:06:47,363
It's hot.

112
00:06:47,403 --> 00:06:48,695
Got it.

113
00:06:48,945 --> 00:06:50,278
I got it.

114
00:06:52,073 --> 00:06:53,440
(Sighs)

115
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,008
Is it tough doing these interviews?

116
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:58,190
(Sighs)

117
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:03,240
They've been pestering me for days,
acting like this is some big deal.

118
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:06,519
The last news segment only
took half a day to shoot.

119
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:10,643
Just bear with it a little longer, okay?

120
00:07:11,477 --> 00:07:15,560
It's great publicity for the studio,
and it isn't easy to get on TV.

121
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,810
I know...

122
00:07:18,394 --> 00:07:21,644
...if it's good for you, I guess it's fine.

123
00:07:23,102 --> 00:07:26,477
But that young producer is such a pain.

124
00:07:26,644 --> 00:07:28,937
Why does she treat me like a kid?

125
00:07:28,977 --> 00:07:31,185
Always bossing me around,
"Do this" or "Do that!"

126
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:35,323
All producers are like that,
don't let it bother you.

127
00:07:35,526 --> 00:07:36,862
(Chuckles)

128
00:07:37,258 --> 00:07:38,258
You're right.

129
00:07:39,019 --> 00:07:40,644
At my age, earning a living...

130
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:44,352
I'm just grateful to be acknowledged.

131
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,343
Do you know how jealous Gyu-chil is of me?

132
00:07:48,448 --> 00:07:49,651
(Chuckles)

133
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:54,804
That guy's broke,
but he's constantly going on trips.

134
00:07:54,845 --> 00:07:57,389
What?
He hasn't come back from Southeast Asia?

135
00:07:57,429 --> 00:07:58,137
No.

136
00:07:58,429 --> 00:08:00,429
I'm so disappointed.

137
00:08:00,842 --> 00:08:03,550
He could've taken you with him,
why'd he go alone?

138
00:08:03,804 --> 00:08:06,470
What for? There's nothing for me to see.

139
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:10,395
You've been friends for decades,
travelling together would've been nice.

140
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,140
He's no friend of mine.

141
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,854
(Chuckles)

142
00:08:15,512 --> 00:08:17,137
Don't say things you don't really mean.

143
00:08:17,276 --> 00:08:17,904
(Lip Smack)

144
00:08:17,929 --> 00:08:20,304
Alright, I've got a call, one moment.

145
00:08:20,345 --> 00:08:21,261
Okay.

146
00:08:21,338 --> 00:08:22,710
(Phone Vibrating)

147
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,222
Hello?

148
00:08:24,262 --> 00:08:26,137
Is this Mr. I'm Dong-hwan?

149
00:08:26,429 --> 00:08:27,429
Yes, who is this?

150
00:08:27,845 --> 00:08:29,929
This is Namil Police Station.

151
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,172
The police station?

152
00:08:32,212 --> 00:08:34,629
We're calling about Jung Young-hee.

153
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,416
Who is that?

154
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:38,418
You don't know Jung Young-hee?

155
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,070
She's your mother.

156
00:08:47,678 --> 00:08:48,303
What?

157
00:09:06,362 --> 00:09:08,510
(Fabric Rustle)

158
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:21,017
You say this is my mother?

159
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:22,166
(Groans)

160
00:09:22,392 --> 00:09:24,475
That's what we presume.

161
00:09:24,850 --> 00:09:27,850
We found an ID card with the remains.

162
00:09:28,350 --> 00:09:32,142
The body was found while excavating
a mountain for a construction site...

163
00:09:32,229 --> 00:09:33,760
(Plastic Rustle)

164
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,965
...and we found personal belongings.

165
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:38,602
Judging by the condition of the remains...

166
00:09:38,642 --> 00:09:40,892
...it's been about 40 years.

167
00:09:41,308 --> 00:09:45,767
The state of the body makes it difficult
to determine the cause of death.

168
00:09:46,017 --> 00:09:49,017
All we know is that she
died 40 years ago...

169
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:51,057
...and was buried in the mountain.

170
00:09:51,088 --> 00:09:52,015
(Long Breath)

171
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:55,790
It's hard to say if it
was an accident or not...

172
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:58,999
...but given how the body was buried...

173
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,084
...there's a chance of foul play.

174
00:10:02,457 --> 00:10:05,832
Even so,
the statute of limitations has long expired.

175
00:10:06,174 --> 00:10:07,523
(Sighs)

176
00:10:17,749 --> 00:10:21,996
National ID: Jung Young-hee.

177
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:26,120
Funeral Home.

178
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,979
(Footstep)

179
00:10:32,332 --> 00:10:34,582
Don't work too hard, no one's here anyway.

180
00:10:35,002 --> 00:10:36,302
(Indistinct)

181
00:10:41,791 --> 00:10:42,665
(Indistinct Utensil Clatter)

182
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:43,885
(Sighs)

183
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:45,729
(Indistinct)

184
00:10:49,456 --> 00:10:50,456
Is that you?

185
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,475
Yes.

186
00:10:51,850 --> 00:10:52,850
Okay.

187
00:10:53,198 --> 00:10:53,974
(Groans)

188
00:10:53,999 --> 00:10:55,624
Anyone from the association here?

189
00:10:55,749 --> 00:10:59,040
Not yet, they sent a wreath though.

190
00:11:00,838 --> 00:11:01,862
(Groans)

191
00:11:02,932 --> 00:11:03,940
(Sighs)

192
00:11:04,854 --> 00:11:05,768
(Sighs)

193
00:11:07,687 --> 00:11:08,599
(Gasps)

194
00:11:08,624 --> 00:11:10,165
- Father.
- Yeah?

195
00:11:12,374 --> 00:11:14,124
Wasn't it that...

196
00:11:15,165 --> 00:11:19,415
...mother just ran away, leaving us behind?

197
00:11:20,707 --> 00:11:22,624
That's what I thought too.

198
00:11:26,915 --> 00:11:29,790
I came home from work...

199
00:11:30,457 --> 00:11:32,290
...and only you were in the room...

200
00:11:32,415 --> 00:11:34,540
...she wasn't there.

201
00:11:35,582 --> 00:11:38,415
And... that was it.

202
00:11:39,327 --> 00:11:40,046
(Lip Smack)

203
00:11:40,915 --> 00:11:45,624
No one came looking for
her or anything like that?

204
00:11:46,165 --> 00:11:47,332
Not at all.

205
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:52,790
Neither of us had any family to speak of...

206
00:11:53,999 --> 00:11:59,915
She wouldn't have had any enemies, right?

207
00:12:01,165 --> 00:12:02,415
Of course not.

208
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:06,198
Your mother was such a kind person.

209
00:12:06,582 --> 00:12:07,957
You know...

210
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,210
Why would you say that?

211
00:12:10,264 --> 00:12:11,431
It's nothing.

212
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,538
It's just...

213
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:18,305
...after 40 years,
suddenly hearing that she passed away...

214
00:12:18,346 --> 00:12:20,513
...I was just curious,
don't worry about it.

215
00:12:21,007 --> 00:12:21,812
(Gasps)

216
00:12:24,696 --> 00:12:25,571
Excuse me.

217
00:12:27,573 --> 00:12:30,490
We have guests, father. The producer.

218
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,000
Please come in.

219
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,743
I should've prepared this.

220
00:12:36,218 --> 00:12:37,272
(Long Breath)

221
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:38,870
(Gasps)

222
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:46,182
For this to happen in
the middle of filming...

223
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:48,392
...I don't know what to say.

224
00:12:48,432 --> 00:12:51,057
I'm really sorry about this.

225
00:12:51,082 --> 00:12:51,749
(Sighs)

226
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,747
It seems this will disrupt the broadcast...

227
00:12:55,539 --> 00:12:56,159
...is that okay?

228
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,950
We can't have disruptions.

229
00:12:58,663 --> 00:13:00,997
We'll stick with you until the end.

230
00:13:02,497 --> 00:13:03,124
Pardon?

231
00:13:03,164 --> 00:13:05,205
As I mentioned before...

232
00:13:05,372 --> 00:13:09,372
...the schedule's finalized,
and delaying it isn't an option.

233
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:15,288
Besides, these moments might feel
more authentic to the viewers.

234
00:13:16,538 --> 00:13:17,429
(Scoffs)

235
00:13:18,647 --> 00:13:19,897
Well, but...

236
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:20,866
(Gasps)

237
00:13:21,413 --> 00:13:24,080
I mean, it's just a bit...

238
00:13:24,663 --> 00:13:26,372
Don't worry.

239
00:13:26,622 --> 00:13:28,663
We'll handle everything.

240
00:13:29,413 --> 00:13:30,705
Alright, but...

241
00:13:30,937 --> 00:13:31,960
(Sighs)

242
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,205
...my father might feel differently.

243
00:13:35,247 --> 00:13:36,913
I'm counting on you.

244
00:13:38,663 --> 00:13:40,413
This must be the place.

245
00:13:40,546 --> 00:13:42,210
(Footstep)

246
00:13:45,288 --> 00:13:48,350
Please have some. I'll be right back.

247
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:51,202
(Footstep)

248
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,538
Hello.

249
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,747
May I help you?

250
00:13:55,122 --> 00:13:57,247
He must be the son.

251
00:13:58,122 --> 00:14:00,788
I'm your aunt, we're Young-hee's sisters.

252
00:14:09,444 --> 00:14:10,638
(Indistinct)

253
00:14:10,678 --> 00:14:12,970
After getting a call from the police...

254
00:14:14,997 --> 00:14:19,122
...we thought it was
the right thing to come here.

255
00:14:19,205 --> 00:14:23,413
She was my aunt, after all.

256
00:14:23,497 --> 00:14:24,705
I see.

257
00:14:25,538 --> 00:14:29,663
I also want to sincerely pay my respects.

258
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:32,872
Thank you all for coming.

259
00:14:35,538 --> 00:14:36,530
(Sighs)

260
00:14:37,491 --> 00:14:38,796
(Slurping Liquid)

261
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,734
Also...

262
00:14:41,859 --> 00:14:44,900
...we came here to clarify something.

263
00:14:45,525 --> 00:14:48,194
My grandfather left a small inheritance...

264
00:14:48,234 --> 00:14:53,400
...to my mother and your mother...

265
00:14:54,109 --> 00:14:56,734
...but we're not willing to share that.

266
00:14:59,405 --> 00:15:00,319
(Scoffs)

267
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:01,596
Pardon?

268
00:15:01,721 --> 00:15:05,055
From what my mother told me...

269
00:15:05,096 --> 00:15:09,390
...your mother left home
when she was very young...

270
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:12,680
...so, she had no interaction
with us - - I see, I see.

271
00:15:13,799 --> 00:15:16,799
I'm a bit taken aback,
but I don't need the money.

272
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,898
This is all so sudden...

273
00:15:21,202 --> 00:15:22,397
(Chuckles)

274
00:15:23,055 --> 00:15:27,971
Besides, discussing money at a time
like this doesn't seem right.

275
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:30,721
You're okay with that, right?

276
00:15:32,388 --> 00:15:33,388
Okay.

277
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,513
I'm sorry about that.

278
00:15:41,430 --> 00:15:43,971
I thought you'd agree to it.

279
00:15:44,263 --> 00:15:46,638
In that case,
would it be okay to record this conver -.

280
00:15:46,679 --> 00:15:47,762
Please!

281
00:15:49,296 --> 00:15:49,988
(Gasps)

282
00:15:50,013 --> 00:15:51,138
Later...

283
00:15:52,513 --> 00:15:55,471
...I'll write a formal statement...

284
00:15:55,888 --> 00:15:58,346
...and get it notarized.

285
00:15:58,763 --> 00:16:00,305
I'll send it by courier.

286
00:16:01,471 --> 00:16:02,346
Good?

287
00:16:02,513 --> 00:16:03,805
Very well.

288
00:16:04,388 --> 00:16:05,680
My apologies.

289
00:16:05,866 --> 00:16:06,897
(Sighs)

290
00:16:08,655 --> 00:16:09,694
(Tch)

291
00:16:09,971 --> 00:16:11,973
I don't need anything...

292
00:16:12,013 --> 00:16:16,430
...but I feel awful about holding
her funeral without a photo...

293
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:17,663
(Gasps)

294
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:20,056
...so, let me ask you for a favour.

295
00:16:20,096 --> 00:16:21,973
If you have a photo of her...

296
00:16:22,013 --> 00:16:24,596
...could you please share it with me?

297
00:16:26,513 --> 00:16:27,765
There aren't any.

298
00:16:27,805 --> 00:16:28,888
No photos of her.

299
00:16:29,305 --> 00:16:30,096
What?

300
00:16:30,930 --> 00:16:32,096
They don't exist.

301
00:16:32,721 --> 00:16:34,596
She didn't like taking photos.

302
00:16:36,305 --> 00:16:37,805
Her face was...

303
00:16:38,013 --> 00:16:40,263
...a bit ugly...

304
00:16:42,555 --> 00:16:44,555
I guess you wouldn't know.

305
00:16:45,013 --> 00:16:46,263
Young-hee...

306
00:16:46,444 --> 00:16:47,116
(Sighs)

307
00:16:47,388 --> 00:16:49,471
...didn't like taking photos...

308
00:16:50,013 --> 00:16:53,221
...because she was ugly.

309
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:02,680
The First Interview.

310
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,441
Ugly?

311
00:17:07,816 --> 00:17:09,733
What do you mean by that?

312
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:15,275
Did she have some kind of disability?

313
00:17:15,775 --> 00:17:18,150
She had her shortcomings...

314
00:17:18,316 --> 00:17:21,233
...but it's not like she
was a gimp or anything.

315
00:17:22,525 --> 00:17:24,568
She was just ugly, that's all.

316
00:17:24,608 --> 00:17:27,566
Why do you keep saying that?

317
00:17:28,525 --> 00:17:29,858
Seriously, even just now...

318
00:17:30,691 --> 00:17:33,275
...you said she ran
away when she was a kid.

319
00:17:33,691 --> 00:17:34,236
Yeah.

320
00:17:34,276 --> 00:17:36,441
She just ran away from home like that?

321
00:17:36,566 --> 00:17:38,691
Yeah, she just left without any warning.

322
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:40,566
That makes sense to you?

323
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:43,441
A little kid? Running away for no reason?

324
00:17:43,816 --> 00:17:45,193
You never suspected anything?

325
00:17:45,233 --> 00:17:47,858
She could've been kidnapped, even.

326
00:17:48,191 --> 00:17:52,066
What kind of lunatic would
kidnap a girl so ugly?

327
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:53,858
She just up and left!

328
00:17:53,983 --> 00:17:56,191
Young-hee, she...

329
00:17:56,816 --> 00:18:00,358
...told weird stories to the neighbours.

330
00:18:00,779 --> 00:18:02,696
What kind of stories?

331
00:18:02,741 --> 00:18:03,694
(Sighs)

332
00:18:03,858 --> 00:18:05,900
She claimed...

333
00:18:06,275 --> 00:18:11,191
...she saw father with another woman,
both undressed...

334
00:18:11,983 --> 00:18:13,900
...at his real estate office.

335
00:18:14,227 --> 00:18:15,000
(Sighs)

336
00:18:15,025 --> 00:18:17,733
So, mother got angry...

337
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:21,358
...and beat her really badly.

338
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:26,003
Afterward, she was sick for a few days...

339
00:18:27,191 --> 00:18:28,483
...then she just left.

340
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:31,150
She didn't just leave...

341
00:18:31,275 --> 00:18:34,691
...she took all of mother's
jewellery and valuables.

342
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:38,276
To mother,
she wasn't a daughter - she was a thief.

343
00:18:38,316 --> 00:18:39,608
That's not right.

344
00:18:41,941 --> 00:18:44,733
If a husband is cheating...

345
00:18:45,066 --> 00:18:47,401
...he's the one who should be blamed.

346
00:18:47,441 --> 00:18:49,318
Beating up a child for speaking up?

347
00:18:49,358 --> 00:18:51,110
Isn't that the mother's fault?

348
00:18:51,150 --> 00:18:53,858
We were a perfectly happy family...

349
00:18:54,150 --> 00:18:57,233
...and that freak of a girl
destroyed it with her rumours...

350
00:18:57,316 --> 00:18:59,526
...of course she should be beaten
within an inch of her life!

351
00:18:59,566 --> 00:19:01,110
Don't talk like that!

352
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:02,441
In any case...

353
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:06,650
...that's all we know about Young-hee.

354
00:19:07,650 --> 00:19:08,983
After that...

355
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:12,108
...we lost contact with her.

356
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,110
With all the jewellery she took...

357
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:16,525
...she got more than her
share of inheritance.

358
00:19:17,316 --> 00:19:19,733
She was family in name only.

359
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:24,051
We've done our part by coming here...

360
00:19:24,385 --> 00:19:26,135
...haven't we?

361
00:19:26,301 --> 00:19:27,843
That's right, Aunt.

362
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,960
Should we get going, then?

363
00:19:31,018 --> 00:19:32,393
Yes, let's go.

364
00:19:33,038 --> 00:19:33,550
(Clearing Throat)

365
00:19:49,260 --> 00:19:50,510
Yes, boss.

366
00:19:50,676 --> 00:19:53,093
Sir, you've got to trust me on this one.

367
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:58,051
I think the story of his
wife is even more compelling.

368
00:19:58,676 --> 00:20:01,093
I've got a strong feeling...

369
00:20:01,343 --> 00:20:05,010
...that we've hit on
a much bigger story here.

370
00:20:07,968 --> 00:20:09,551
I'm sure of it.

371
00:20:09,726 --> 00:20:12,059
It's an undeniably gripping story.

372
00:20:13,518 --> 00:20:17,893
Entertaining? Absolutely!

373
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,885
Then I'll get to work.

374
00:20:23,343 --> 00:20:26,760
Okay, thank you, bye.

375
00:20:47,104 --> 00:20:48,455
(Thud)

376
00:20:52,593 --> 00:20:54,468
You can stand here.

377
00:20:54,857 --> 00:20:57,256
(Metal Clinking)

378
00:20:59,069 --> 00:21:01,999
(Footstep)

379
00:21:08,858 --> 00:21:09,827
(Coughs)

380
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:13,547
Well...

381
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:18,131
...this is my first time
shrouding a skeleton...

382
00:21:19,421 --> 00:21:22,213
...but I've done my best to
piece the bones together.

383
00:21:22,796 --> 00:21:25,796
If you wish to say any final words,
please do so now.

384
00:21:29,091 --> 00:21:30,260
There isn't much...

385
00:21:30,380 --> 00:21:32,088
...Young-hee, rest in peace.

386
00:21:32,505 --> 00:21:33,965
If you two have anything to say...

387
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:35,506
...make it quick so we can leave.

388
00:21:35,546 --> 00:21:37,255
I've got a weak stomach.

389
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:38,297
(Grunts)

390
00:21:47,005 --> 00:21:49,296
If there's nothing to say,
let's just end it.

391
00:21:49,588 --> 00:21:51,046
I'm feeling nauseous.

392
00:21:51,484 --> 00:21:52,617
(Thud)

393
00:21:52,664 --> 00:21:54,992
(Grunts)

394
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:57,304
(Thud)

395
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:02,120
(Groans)

396
00:22:03,505 --> 00:22:05,505
Seriously...

397
00:22:06,272 --> 00:22:09,022
Do you know how long it
took to put this together?

398
00:22:09,505 --> 00:22:11,671
It'll all be cremated anyway.

399
00:22:12,001 --> 00:22:13,126
But I'm sorry...

400
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,917
...I can't take it any more.

401
00:22:16,338 --> 00:22:17,546
Christ...

402
00:22:18,088 --> 00:22:20,338
Father, don't worry, it's nothing.

403
00:22:22,130 --> 00:22:23,796
Are you okay?

404
00:22:27,671 --> 00:22:28,630
One moment.

405
00:22:29,989 --> 00:22:33,447
- Father, I need to take a call.
- Sure, sure.

406
00:22:33,508 --> 00:22:34,672
(Cane Tapping)

407
00:22:34,882 --> 00:22:38,749
(Footstep)

408
00:22:39,088 --> 00:22:39,965
Hello, Producer Kim.

409
00:22:40,005 --> 00:22:41,963
Hello? So...

410
00:22:42,588 --> 00:22:47,130
You know the commercial building
where your parents first met?

411
00:22:47,296 --> 00:22:48,171
Pardon?

412
00:22:48,213 --> 00:22:52,755
The one in the photo,
in front of the stamp stand.

413
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:55,691
Yes, what about it?

414
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:58,620
I asked around and found out...

415
00:22:58,671 --> 00:23:03,755
...she worked at a factory in that
building called CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS.

416
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:08,635
CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS?

417
00:23:08,713 --> 00:23:09,880
Yes, yes.

418
00:23:10,213 --> 00:23:13,338
CHEONGPUNG ENGRAVING, CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS.

419
00:23:14,463 --> 00:23:15,880
Isn't that interesting?

420
00:23:16,463 --> 00:23:20,046
Yes, I guess...

421
00:23:20,124 --> 00:23:20,770
(Gasps)

422
00:23:20,795 --> 00:23:25,671
I got in touch with a few
factory workers from back then.

423
00:23:25,755 --> 00:23:28,463
They said they knew your mother.

424
00:23:29,088 --> 00:23:29,965
So...

425
00:23:30,005 --> 00:23:33,297
...if you're free tomorrow...

426
00:23:33,338 --> 00:23:37,088
...how about joining us
for a chat with them?

427
00:23:49,130 --> 00:23:49,799
Is that good?

428
00:23:49,839 --> 00:23:50,880
Like this?

429
00:23:51,187 --> 00:23:52,640
(Clatter)

430
00:23:54,338 --> 00:23:55,338
Let me see.

431
00:23:59,484 --> 00:24:01,108
(Birds Chirping)

432
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,734
Stay in the van.

433
00:24:04,804 --> 00:24:06,445
(Footstep)

434
00:24:06,623 --> 00:24:07,831
Good to see you.

435
00:24:09,343 --> 00:24:10,295
(Car Door Closes In Distant)

436
00:24:10,328 --> 00:24:11,745
Ms. Kim...

437
00:24:12,562 --> 00:24:14,645
...I appreciate the gesture, but...

438
00:24:14,879 --> 00:24:16,215
Don't mention it!

439
00:24:16,255 --> 00:24:18,546
No, that's not what I'm saying.

440
00:24:20,255 --> 00:24:21,923
You don't have to go this far.

441
00:24:21,963 --> 00:24:23,006
No, no.

442
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:27,662
I'm a journalist at heart,
digging into a story is so much fun.

443
00:24:27,976 --> 00:24:31,185
Let's go in! The elders are waiting.

444
00:24:31,296 --> 00:24:33,546
Okay? Come on.

445
00:24:37,130 --> 00:24:40,046
The Second Interview.

446
00:24:40,101 --> 00:24:41,437
(Door Opens)

447
00:24:42,859 --> 00:24:44,374
(Indistinct Chatter)

448
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,183
Good afternoon.

449
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:47,957
Hi.

450
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:49,517
Have a seat.

451
00:24:49,563 --> 00:24:50,493
(Indistinct)

452
00:24:52,681 --> 00:24:53,743
(Thud)

453
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:56,177
What can I get you two?

454
00:24:56,225 --> 00:24:57,850
Anything will be fine.

455
00:24:58,017 --> 00:24:59,767
Juice would be great.

456
00:24:59,850 --> 00:25:01,308
Very well.

457
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:06,345
I'm Kim Su-jin...

458
00:25:06,385 --> 00:25:08,927
...the producer who contacted you.

459
00:25:10,385 --> 00:25:11,385
Here.

460
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:14,385
And who's he?

461
00:25:16,135 --> 00:25:18,135
This is, uh...

462
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,085
I'm the writer.

463
00:25:20,594 --> 00:25:22,960
- A writer?
- Is that so?

464
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:24,895
Yes, our writer.

465
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:28,405
So, you're a TV producer?

466
00:25:28,969 --> 00:25:30,719
Is this for the news?

467
00:25:30,885 --> 00:25:32,635
Yes, something like that.

468
00:25:32,802 --> 00:25:37,719
We're investigating the story
of Ms. Jung Young-hee.

469
00:25:38,635 --> 00:25:41,469
Her remains were discovered...

470
00:25:41,677 --> 00:25:45,885
...near the garment factory
where you all used to work.

471
00:25:46,010 --> 00:25:48,635
It seems she died about 40 years ago.

472
00:25:49,177 --> 00:25:50,010
Oh dear...

473
00:25:50,219 --> 00:25:51,304
When you called...

474
00:25:51,344 --> 00:25:54,719
...we assumed she died some place far away.

475
00:25:54,876 --> 00:25:55,938
(Gasps)

476
00:25:56,028 --> 00:26:00,611
Back then she just vanished,
so we thought she'd run away.

477
00:26:01,919 --> 00:26:04,313
Seems she met some terrible misfortune.

478
00:26:04,524 --> 00:26:05,069
(Tch)

479
00:26:05,094 --> 00:26:06,219
Oh dear...

480
00:26:06,969 --> 00:26:10,677
She just stopped coming
to the factory one day?

481
00:26:11,219 --> 00:26:14,844
Yes, so we thought she had run away.

482
00:26:15,923 --> 00:26:16,673
(Glass Clinking)

483
00:26:16,969 --> 00:26:18,160
Was there...

484
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:22,352
...anyone at the factory...

485
00:26:22,510 --> 00:26:26,344
...who was close to her by any chance?

486
00:26:26,844 --> 00:26:28,260
Well...

487
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:31,861
...the only person close to Dung Ogre...

488
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:36,945
...was the blind guy who
ended up marrying her.

489
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,137
"Dung Ogre"?

490
00:26:39,516 --> 00:26:40,309
That's...

491
00:26:40,392 --> 00:26:42,476
We called her "Dung Ogre"...

492
00:26:42,679 --> 00:26:45,129
...because of her face and all.

493
00:26:45,181 --> 00:26:46,654
(Chuckles)

494
00:26:46,679 --> 00:26:48,512
Come on now.

495
00:26:48,537 --> 00:26:49,142
(Click)

496
00:26:49,262 --> 00:26:52,220
No one literally looks like dung...

497
00:26:53,012 --> 00:26:57,262
...but there was a reason
behind the nickname.

498
00:26:57,353 --> 00:26:58,485
(Chuckles)

499
00:26:58,554 --> 00:27:00,220
What reason was that?

500
00:27:01,329 --> 00:27:02,720
(Chuckles)

501
00:27:02,804 --> 00:27:04,012
I can't...

502
00:27:04,679 --> 00:27:07,345
Come on, you can tell me.

503
00:27:07,673 --> 00:27:08,774
It's all in the past.

504
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:11,690
Back then...

505
00:27:11,730 --> 00:27:14,188
...everything was so hectic.

506
00:27:15,320 --> 00:27:17,611
It was a real boom period.

507
00:27:17,796 --> 00:27:21,379
We were so busy, every day was a whirlwind.

508
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:22,824
(Indistinct Chatter)

509
00:27:22,849 --> 00:27:27,308
The country was literally on the rise.

510
00:27:32,923 --> 00:27:35,345
(Indistinct Chatter)

511
00:27:45,532 --> 00:27:47,657
(Indistinct Chatter)

512
00:28:08,688 --> 00:28:10,746
(Indistinct Chatter)

513
00:28:10,771 --> 00:28:12,896
CHEONGPUNG GARMENTS

514
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:17,936
Young-hee! What took you so long?!

515
00:28:18,297 --> 00:28:21,464
Hurry up and bring the fabric!
Move your ass, will you!

516
00:28:21,868 --> 00:28:23,532
(Sewing Machine Whirring)

517
00:28:25,712 --> 00:28:27,970
(Indistinct Chatter)

518
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:33,142
(Iron Steaming)

519
00:28:33,579 --> 00:28:35,714
(Indistinct Chatter)

520
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,708
Hey, I told you to clear this away.

521
00:28:44,605 --> 00:28:47,021
You've been messing with this all day!

522
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:49,758
(Gasps)

523
00:28:50,438 --> 00:28:53,271
Excuse me, boss...

524
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,950
I'm sorry, but...

525
00:28:56,908 --> 00:28:58,866
...could I use the bathroom...?

526
00:28:59,325 --> 00:29:01,909
We're drowning in work, there's no time!

527
00:29:01,950 --> 00:29:03,700
I-I'm sorry...

528
00:29:04,376 --> 00:29:05,704
(Whimpering)

529
00:29:05,783 --> 00:29:07,700
It's urgent...

530
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,207
Get back here in one minute.

531
00:29:10,430 --> 00:29:11,650
Thank you.

532
00:29:12,845 --> 00:29:15,040
(Panting)

533
00:29:21,103 --> 00:29:23,063
(Groans)

534
00:29:27,366 --> 00:29:29,226
Toilet.

535
00:29:31,063 --> 00:29:33,587
(Groans)

536
00:29:36,743 --> 00:29:37,651
(Pants)

537
00:29:43,092 --> 00:29:44,673
(Groans)

538
00:29:48,602 --> 00:29:51,524
(Chuckles)

539
00:29:51,616 --> 00:29:56,533
She took his words literally,
and had no time to poop.

540
00:29:57,158 --> 00:30:00,450
She stupidly ended up going in her pants.

541
00:30:00,475 --> 00:30:01,312
(Chuckles)

542
00:30:07,991 --> 00:30:09,950
Clean it up now!

543
00:30:13,825 --> 00:30:17,366
It was such a strange and pitiful sight.

544
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:19,883
Her face was bad enough...

545
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:23,520
...but then to poop her pants...

546
00:30:24,116 --> 00:30:27,950
Everyone called her "Dung Ogre" after that.

547
00:30:33,658 --> 00:30:38,118
What exactly did she look like...

548
00:30:38,159 --> 00:30:41,159
...for people to talk about
her appearance so much?

549
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:45,931
Did she have a facial deformity
or something like that?

550
00:30:45,971 --> 00:30:47,221
A deformity?

551
00:30:47,888 --> 00:30:53,096
It's hard to describe
what she looked like...

